[See map: https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/02/26/19/wire-39813532-1614367679-314_634x599.jpg, where Guinea's latest Ebola outbreak occurred.

The response this time was very fast. But the problem now seems to fall on diagnosis: early and rapid diagnosis is needed to prevent a patient from going to multiple healthcare centers for medical help. If rapid tests were in stock in clinics in countries where Ebola is enzootic/endemic and doctors were trained to use them if Ebola is even remotely suspected when the patient presents with fever and bleeding, that would be a good practice. It could prevent spread beyond the initial site. - Mod LK]

